WEBVTT

00:06.291 --> 00:07.375
[dog barking distantly]

00:07.458 --> 00:10.041
[Alice] Men are gonna come along
and wanna teach you things.

00:10.625 --> 00:12.208
Doesn't make them any smarter.

00:13.083 --> 00:16.083
In most ways, they're not,
but it makes them feel bigger.

00:16.916 --> 00:19.250
They can show you how things are done.

00:19.791 --> 00:21.291
You just let them blow by,

00:21.375 --> 00:24.625
and you go on ahead,
and do just what the hell you feel like.

00:26.000 --> 00:28.666
It takes a strong woman
to stay by herself,

00:28.750 --> 00:32.000
in a world where people
will settle for anything,

00:32.083 --> 00:33.833
just to say they have something.

00:35.416 --> 00:36.375
There we are.

00:37.958 --> 00:39.708
So you never forget who you are.

00:40.708 --> 00:42.375
["Stop Your Sobbing" by The Kinks playing]

00:42.458 --> 00:46.916
♪ …for you to stop all of your sobbin' ♪

00:48.666 --> 00:52.041
♪ Yes, it's time for you to stop ♪

00:52.625 --> 00:56.041
♪ All of your sobbin', ooh ♪

00:57.000 --> 00:59.583
[both singing along]
♪ There's one thing you gotta do ♪

00:59.666 --> 01:01.000
[Beth laughs]

01:01.083 --> 01:04.083
♪ To make me still want you ♪

01:04.166 --> 01:05.291
♪ Gotta stop sobbin' now ♪

01:05.375 --> 01:07.833
-[Benny] Pawn to king four.
-[Beth] Pawn to queen bishop four.

01:07.916 --> 01:09.875
-N to KB-3.
-Pawn to queen three.

01:09.958 --> 01:10.791
P to Q4.

01:11.375 --> 01:12.291
Pawn takes pawn.

01:12.833 --> 01:15.458
-Knight takes.
-Knight… king bishop three.

01:15.541 --> 01:18.000
-[Benny] N to QB-3.
-[Beth] Pawn to king's knight three.

01:18.083 --> 01:19.000
[Benny] P to B4.

01:19.083 --> 01:20.166
[Beth] P to B4.

01:20.250 --> 01:22.833
[Benny] The Levenfish. Never liked it.

01:22.916 --> 01:24.833
-King to B3.
-[Beth] I'll take the knight.

01:24.916 --> 01:26.708
-[Benny] Pawn takes.
-[Beth] Pawn to king five.

01:26.791 --> 01:27.916
Pawn takes again.

01:28.000 --> 01:30.458
Hey, you know what Scharz
says about that in the footnote?

01:30.958 --> 01:32.041
I don't read the footnotes.

01:33.458 --> 01:36.291
-Okay, well, it's time you started.
-I don't like Scharz.

01:36.375 --> 01:38.750
Oh, I don't like Scharz either,
but I read him.

01:40.708 --> 01:41.666
What's your move?

01:44.166 --> 01:45.708
Queen takes queen. Check.

01:45.791 --> 01:47.833
[Benny] The weather is hot today.

01:47.916 --> 01:49.375
[Beth repeats phrase in Russian]

01:49.458 --> 01:50.708
[in English] I feel sick.

01:50.791 --> 01:52.791
Mm. [repeats phrase in Russian]

01:58.125 --> 01:59.750
[quiet, uplifting music playing]

02:26.166 --> 02:27.250
[dog barks distantly]

02:28.000 --> 02:29.000
[Benny] Here you go.

02:44.666 --> 02:45.750
[Benny] Not that one.

02:47.625 --> 02:48.458
This one.

02:51.708 --> 02:53.500
[distant traffic sounds]

03:03.958 --> 03:05.041
[Beth] Benny?

03:06.208 --> 03:07.041
Come on.

03:11.500 --> 03:12.708
[keys jangling]

03:13.291 --> 03:14.833
[man yelling distantly]

03:20.125 --> 03:21.625
-[door opens]
-[light switch clicks]

03:26.541 --> 03:27.500
[Benny sighs]

03:34.333 --> 03:35.250
[Benny sighs]

03:52.291 --> 03:55.125
-Is there a bathroom?
-Oh, yeah, it's just through there.

03:55.208 --> 03:56.375
[water dripping]

04:05.500 --> 04:06.333
[door closes]

04:23.000 --> 04:24.208
There's space in the closet.

04:24.291 --> 04:26.500
You can hang your clothes up
in there if you want.

04:27.250 --> 04:28.083
[Beth] Okay.

04:46.916 --> 04:49.958
-I thought I was gonna get a couch.
-No, I said living room.

04:51.666 --> 04:52.833
Just gotta…

04:53.916 --> 04:54.750
pump it up.

04:54.833 --> 04:57.250
[air blowing]

05:03.208 --> 05:04.875
-I got it.
-Really?

05:04.958 --> 05:07.083
-You sure? Gonna be all right?
-Sure.

05:11.458 --> 05:13.833
Oh, there's no booze in the apartment.

05:14.458 --> 05:15.875
Didn't think there would be.

05:23.708 --> 05:24.583
[door closes]

05:30.625 --> 05:32.250
[air blowing]

05:37.541 --> 05:39.041
[loud traffic noises]

05:40.458 --> 05:41.291
[groans]

05:47.458 --> 05:49.458
[dishes clattering]

05:54.333 --> 05:55.416
[liquid pouring]

06:07.416 --> 06:09.125
You can get changed in my bedroom.

06:11.083 --> 06:12.166
I need a shower.

06:13.541 --> 06:14.500
She's all yours.

06:21.958 --> 06:23.958
[door creaking]

06:26.416 --> 06:27.875
Here, we'll start with these.

06:30.583 --> 06:32.875
"The Hastings Christmas Chess Congress."

06:32.958 --> 06:35.333
"Falaise Hall, White Rock Gardens."

06:35.416 --> 06:36.916
"Record of games."

06:38.041 --> 06:41.083
"Luchenko-Uhlmann. Borgov-Penrose."

06:43.250 --> 06:44.625
"Grandmaster Chess." Whoo!

06:46.500 --> 06:48.125
Play the Hastings games first.

06:48.208 --> 06:49.291
I'll play black.

06:49.375 --> 06:50.791
I haven't had any breakfast.

06:52.708 --> 06:54.041
Eggs are in the fridge.

06:54.125 --> 06:55.000
Thank you.

06:55.083 --> 06:57.083
Then, we'll play the Borgov games first.

06:58.333 --> 07:00.708
-All of them?
-He will be in Paris.

07:00.791 --> 07:01.625
Fine.

07:02.833 --> 07:03.750
I will eat first.

07:06.291 --> 07:07.875
[anticipatory music playing]

07:07.958 --> 07:11.958
[Benny] Why not advance the knight?
Why isn't he defending against the rook?

07:13.000 --> 07:15.333
What's gonna become of the backward pawn?

07:18.833 --> 07:20.041
[air blowing]

07:20.125 --> 07:23.333
You replay the game
so you can feel the wins for yourself.

07:27.166 --> 07:29.166
You read game books like Reinfeld

07:29.250 --> 07:32.250
that are full of queen sacrifices
and melodrama.

07:32.916 --> 07:34.791
You know from your tournament experience

07:34.875 --> 07:39.041
you can't rely on your opponent
setting himself up for a queen sacrifice,

07:39.125 --> 07:41.625
or a surprise mate
with a knight and a rook.

07:41.708 --> 07:44.750
[chess pieces clattering]

07:48.333 --> 07:50.083
-[scoffs]
-[Benny] But that's who you are.

07:50.166 --> 07:51.958
You're bored with ordinary chess,

07:52.041 --> 07:54.333
even when it's played by Grandmasters.

07:58.875 --> 08:00.458
You're bored in the way you probably were

08:00.541 --> 08:03.083
when you read
Reuben Fine's endgame analysis.

08:03.166 --> 08:05.291
And then the counter analysis
in Chess Review

08:05.375 --> 08:07.208
that pointed out the errors
in Reuben Fine.

08:07.291 --> 08:08.416
-Benny…
-[tapping page]

08:09.291 --> 08:10.125
…look at this.

08:11.791 --> 08:13.083
Fine missed one.

08:14.125 --> 08:15.125
Look. Ready?

08:16.416 --> 08:17.375
Black…

08:18.583 --> 08:19.666
has this…

08:20.916 --> 08:21.750
with the knight.

08:26.416 --> 08:28.041
-Yeah.
-It's good, it's good! [laughs]

08:28.125 --> 08:29.875
Yeah. Yeah.

08:30.833 --> 08:31.666
Huh.

08:36.666 --> 08:40.125
[Benny] And you haven't done anything
like what I'm making you do now.

08:41.583 --> 08:43.500
We're playing serious chess.

08:44.833 --> 08:46.833
Workmanlike chess.

08:46.916 --> 08:49.833
The kind of chess played
by the best players in the world,

08:49.916 --> 08:50.833
the Soviets.

08:53.375 --> 08:56.083
And you know why
they're the best players in the world?

08:56.166 --> 08:58.000
They have the best suits?

08:58.083 --> 09:00.375
It's because they play together as a team,

09:01.041 --> 09:02.708
especially during adjournments.

09:04.416 --> 09:05.541
They help each other out.

09:05.625 --> 09:10.208
Us Americans, we work alone
because we're all such individualists.

09:10.708 --> 09:12.708
We don't like to let anyone help us.

09:13.416 --> 09:15.041
[yawning] You're helping me now.

09:15.125 --> 09:16.166
Am I?

09:17.416 --> 09:19.541
'Cause it looks more
like I'm putting you to sleep.

09:20.375 --> 09:21.333
I'm sorry.

09:22.041 --> 09:22.875
I'm tired.

09:23.833 --> 09:25.250
I should probably go to bed.

09:26.291 --> 09:28.083
What, and miss out on all the fun?

09:28.166 --> 09:29.791
Mm. I'll survive.

09:35.583 --> 09:36.458
What fun?

09:36.541 --> 09:37.458
[knocking on door]

09:38.333 --> 09:39.916
I wonder who that could be.

09:43.708 --> 09:45.791
[Benny and men] Hey!

09:45.875 --> 09:47.416
[Benny] Right on time.

09:47.500 --> 09:49.916
-Come on in, come on in.
-[man] Good to see you.

09:50.750 --> 09:55.416
Beth Harmon, this is Hilton Wexler
and Grandmaster Arthur Levertov.

09:56.666 --> 09:57.500
The new champ.

09:57.583 --> 09:58.708
Hi.

09:58.791 --> 10:01.166
Congratulations.
Benny needed a lesson in humility.

10:01.250 --> 10:03.791
-[Beth laughs]
-[Benny] I'm already tops in humility.

10:03.875 --> 10:04.875
Hello, Beth.

10:05.833 --> 10:07.250
-[kisses]
-Uh… oh…

10:07.333 --> 10:08.166
I'm Cleo.

10:08.250 --> 10:09.083
Hi.

10:10.291 --> 10:11.375
[Hilton] Do you do problems?

10:12.291 --> 10:13.958
-No.
-Never?

10:14.041 --> 10:15.708
I always found them irrelevant.

10:15.791 --> 10:18.541
Positions that never come up
in actual games.

10:18.625 --> 10:19.458
[laughs]

10:20.250 --> 10:21.708
Let me show you one you might like.

10:22.541 --> 10:23.375
Okay.

10:23.875 --> 10:26.125
-Can I mess this up?
-Go ahead.

10:26.208 --> 10:28.458
Hilton, she is not
one of your problem freaks.

10:28.541 --> 10:31.041
-She's the US Champion, for Christ's sake.
-It's okay.

10:31.125 --> 10:33.750
-This one is…
-[pieces clattering]

10:34.833 --> 10:37.375
…my favorite.

10:38.291 --> 10:39.875
How does White win in three?

10:42.041 --> 10:43.000
[crash]

10:43.083 --> 10:45.416
Benny, under what mound
do you hide your drinking glasses?

10:45.500 --> 10:47.000
Hey, quit distracting her.

10:47.583 --> 10:48.500
She's not.

10:48.583 --> 10:50.125
[glasses clinking softly]

10:52.875 --> 10:54.291
King to queen seven.

10:54.375 --> 10:56.125
Jesus! That's fast.

10:57.000 --> 10:57.958
Drink?

11:01.416 --> 11:02.916
No, thank you.

11:04.500 --> 11:06.166
I should fix the food.

11:09.416 --> 11:11.083
Come on, that's enough of that.

11:11.166 --> 11:14.500
-Come on.
-[Arthur] Do you ever clean? [laughs]

11:14.583 --> 11:16.750
Are you here with Arthur or Hilton?

11:17.375 --> 11:18.333
Both of them.

11:19.083 --> 11:20.125
Neither of them.

11:20.958 --> 11:23.458
Two of them are better than one,
if you know what I mean.

11:24.375 --> 11:27.125
-[men chatting indistinctly]
-How do you all know each other?

11:27.833 --> 11:29.166
A sad story,

11:29.750 --> 11:32.208
involving me, a bad breakup,

11:32.291 --> 11:34.458
and a walk through
le Jardin du Luxembourg,

11:34.541 --> 11:37.375
where those two stopped me
from killing myself.

11:39.041 --> 11:40.791
Like I say, a sad story.

11:42.625 --> 11:44.458
But as I walked past,

11:44.541 --> 11:47.958
Arthur and Hilton were having
a violent argument over a chessboard,

11:48.041 --> 11:51.166
and I became mesmerized by their passion.

11:51.250 --> 11:53.166
Well, that's how they tell it, anyway.

11:53.250 --> 11:54.166
[both laugh]

11:54.250 --> 11:56.291
No, the truth is, um…

11:56.375 --> 11:59.291
Benny was there,
and I became mesmerized by Benny.

12:01.750 --> 12:02.958
Over and done.

12:03.041 --> 12:04.166
What do you do?

12:05.708 --> 12:06.541
Guess.

12:07.875 --> 12:09.458
Something in fashion?

12:09.541 --> 12:12.291
[chuckles] That's a nice way to put it.

12:13.458 --> 12:14.416
I'm a model.

12:15.250 --> 12:17.125
-[lighter clicks]
-Wow. [sighs]

12:17.750 --> 12:19.166
That must be exciting.

12:19.250 --> 12:23.291
Fashion is exciting.
Modeling and models are insipid.

12:24.375 --> 12:26.375
But it pays for my studio in the Marais.

12:27.625 --> 12:29.208
Oh, you have not been to Paris?

12:29.750 --> 12:30.583
Not yet.

12:31.208 --> 12:33.416
-Do you live there?
-Sometimes.

12:33.500 --> 12:35.750
Sometimes Berlin, sometimes here.

12:35.833 --> 12:37.125
I'm a, uh…

12:37.958 --> 12:41.125
-how do you say? A vagabond?
-[laughs] I don't know.

12:41.791 --> 12:44.000
Modeling sounds pretty exciting to me.

12:45.708 --> 12:48.416
Plus, I imagine
they give you a lot of free clothes.

12:48.500 --> 12:50.333
Ah, you like nice clothes, huh?

12:50.833 --> 12:52.083
-I do.
-[chuckles]

12:52.583 --> 12:54.208
You could never be a model.

12:55.750 --> 12:58.208
You are pretty enough,
but you are much too smart.

12:58.291 --> 12:59.875
Models are empty creatures.

12:59.958 --> 13:03.291
The camera lens fills them
with color and texture,

13:03.375 --> 13:05.333
and, once in a while, even mystery.

13:05.958 --> 13:08.416
But just like there is no mystery
to a vacant lot,

13:08.500 --> 13:11.708
it's just there until you put
something interesting on top of it…

13:12.666 --> 13:13.875
Models are the same.

13:15.000 --> 13:16.750
They are just what you put on them.

13:18.500 --> 13:20.250
You know, most are terrible in bed.

13:21.708 --> 13:25.125
But then, anyone who doesn't eat
is terrible in bed, don't you think?

13:26.208 --> 13:27.083
[laughs]

13:29.541 --> 13:30.458
[Beth] Here we go.

13:30.541 --> 13:32.041
[upbeat music playing softly]

13:42.416 --> 13:43.416
What?

13:44.625 --> 13:46.625
Let's do a simultaneous.

13:47.208 --> 13:48.166
You…

13:48.666 --> 13:49.666
play all of us.

13:49.750 --> 13:52.083
[Cleo] Uh, not me.
I don't even know the rules.

13:52.166 --> 13:53.500
I'll spectate.

13:54.375 --> 13:57.500
-Do we have enough boards, enough pieces?
-Yeah, in the closet.

13:57.583 --> 13:59.416
We can set them up
right here on the floor.

14:02.250 --> 14:03.250
Okay.

14:03.833 --> 14:06.416
-Time control?
-Let's play speed chess.

14:06.500 --> 14:09.875
Well, that'll give us an edge.
We can think on your time.

14:09.958 --> 14:11.583
Mm. I wanna try it.

14:11.666 --> 14:13.166
You're not so good at that, remember?

14:13.250 --> 14:14.750
I'll bet you ten I can beat you.

14:17.541 --> 14:20.041
What if you throw the other games,
spend all your time against me?

14:20.125 --> 14:22.208
-What if I kick you in the crotch?
-[chuckles]

14:23.625 --> 14:27.250
-[Beth] I'll bet you ten on them, too.
-Okay. It's your money.

14:27.833 --> 14:28.666
It will be.

14:29.541 --> 14:31.416
["Yeh, Yeh" by Georgie Fame playing]

14:34.291 --> 14:37.291
♪ Every evening
When all my day's work is through ♪

14:37.375 --> 14:39.666
♪ I call my baby
And ask her what shall we do ♪

14:39.750 --> 14:42.458
♪ I mention movies
But she don't seem to dig that ♪

14:42.541 --> 14:45.000
♪ And then she asks me
Why don't I come to her flat ♪

14:45.083 --> 14:47.750
♪ And have some supper
And let the evening pass by ♪

14:47.833 --> 14:50.208
♪ By digging records
Beside a groovy hi-fi ♪

14:50.291 --> 14:51.541
♪ I say yeh yeh ♪

14:52.208 --> 14:54.666
♪ That's what I say
I say yeh yeh ♪

14:55.916 --> 14:58.416
♪ My baby loves me
She gets me feeling so fine ♪

14:58.500 --> 15:01.083
♪ Because she loves me
She makes me know that she's mine ♪

15:01.166 --> 15:03.708
♪ And when she kisses
I feel the fire get hot ♪

15:03.791 --> 15:06.291
♪ She never misses
She gives it all that she's got ♪

15:06.375 --> 15:09.375
♪ And when she asks me
If everything is okay ♪

15:09.458 --> 15:11.833
♪ I've got my answer
The only thing I can say ♪

15:11.916 --> 15:13.750
♪ I say yeh yeh ♪

15:13.833 --> 15:16.416
♪ That's what I say
I say yeh yeh ♪

15:18.208 --> 15:22.083
♪ We'll play a melody
And turn the lights down low ♪

15:22.166 --> 15:23.458
♪ So that none can see ♪

15:23.541 --> 15:25.416
♪ We gotta do that
We gotta do that ♪

15:26.000 --> 15:28.000
♪ We gotta do that
We gotta do that ♪

15:28.500 --> 15:33.833
♪ And there'll be no one else alive
In all the world 'cept you and me… ♪

15:33.916 --> 15:34.875
Let's do it again.

15:34.958 --> 15:36.625
♪ Yeh yeh yeh ♪

15:36.708 --> 15:39.125
♪ Yeh yeh yeh yeh
Yeh yeh ♪

15:39.208 --> 15:41.208
[saxophone playing]

16:01.083 --> 16:05.083
♪ We'll play a melody
And turn the lights down low ♪

16:05.166 --> 16:08.083
♪ So that none can see
We gotta do that, we gotta do that ♪

16:08.166 --> 16:11.125
♪ Yeh yeh
We gotta do that, we gotta do that… ♪

16:12.833 --> 16:13.833
Again.

16:13.916 --> 16:16.791
♪ …alive in all the world
'Cept you and me ♪

16:16.875 --> 16:19.625
♪ Yeh yeh yeh yeh
Yeh yeh ♪

16:19.708 --> 16:21.375
♪ Yeh yeh yeh yeh ♪

16:21.458 --> 16:24.083
♪ Pretty baby
I never knew such a thrill ♪

16:24.166 --> 16:26.666
♪ Just thought I'd tell you
Because I'm trembling still ♪

16:26.750 --> 16:29.541
♪ But pretty baby
I want you all for my own ♪

16:29.625 --> 16:32.208
♪ I think I'm ready
To leave those others alone ♪

16:32.291 --> 16:33.666
♪ No need to ask me… ♪

16:33.750 --> 16:34.625
Again.

16:35.166 --> 16:37.416
♪ I got my answer
The only thing I can say ♪

16:37.500 --> 16:39.500
-No.
-♪ I say yeh yeh ♪

16:39.583 --> 16:42.166
♪ That's what I say
I say yeh yeh ♪

16:42.250 --> 16:47.791
♪ That's what I say
I say yeh yeh ♪

16:47.875 --> 16:48.958
♪ Yeh yeh ♪

16:51.875 --> 16:53.166
Well, kid…

16:54.958 --> 16:56.250
I think you've got it.

17:00.375 --> 17:02.083
[all applauding]

17:05.833 --> 17:08.750
It was such a pleasure.
Do look me up if you come to Paris.

17:08.833 --> 17:11.208
-Will you be there in two weeks?
-Oh, who knows?

17:14.250 --> 17:15.583
-Ah, bye.
-[Benny] Bye-bye.

17:20.250 --> 17:22.250
[door closes and locks]

17:25.041 --> 17:27.041
[Benny snapping]

17:28.250 --> 17:29.083
[Beth] What?

17:32.291 --> 17:35.583
Nobody has done that to me in 15 years.

17:36.125 --> 17:37.875
-Not even Borgov?
-Not even Borgov.

17:40.958 --> 17:42.541
And I'm sober as a judge,

17:43.166 --> 17:44.083
as Alma would say.

17:53.208 --> 17:54.416
I, myself, am not.

17:57.333 --> 17:58.166
Good night.

17:59.208 --> 18:00.041
Night.

18:00.833 --> 18:01.750
Wait. Hey.

18:07.416 --> 18:08.250
Yes?

18:12.833 --> 18:14.166
Do you still like my hair?

18:17.125 --> 18:18.000
[sighs]

18:18.625 --> 18:20.625
[Benny and Beth breathing heavily]

18:23.666 --> 18:25.625
That's what it's supposed to feel like.

18:26.958 --> 18:27.875
[moans softly]

18:31.083 --> 18:31.958
Hello?

18:33.833 --> 18:35.291
You should play the Sicilian.

18:37.458 --> 18:38.291
What?

18:39.416 --> 18:42.125
In your game with Borgov,
you should play the Sicilian.

18:44.166 --> 18:45.000
Why?

18:45.583 --> 18:46.916
It's what he's so good at.

18:47.625 --> 18:49.958
It's also
what you're most comfortable with.

18:51.291 --> 18:53.791
You should always
play your line, never his.

18:54.958 --> 18:56.416
You play what's best for you.

18:57.125 --> 18:57.958
Thank you.

18:59.041 --> 18:59.875
Anything else?

19:01.875 --> 19:02.875
One more thing.

19:02.958 --> 19:05.208
They never say "check"
at the big tournaments.

19:07.125 --> 19:08.250
Are you serious?

19:08.333 --> 19:11.208
Yeah, very.
They never lay their kings down, either.

19:11.833 --> 19:13.875
I meant, "Are you serious?"

19:13.958 --> 19:16.291
"This is what you're thinking about
right now?"

19:22.500 --> 19:23.416
Good night, Benny.

19:29.041 --> 19:30.375
[exciting music playing]

19:31.333 --> 19:32.166
Good night.

19:36.708 --> 19:39.500
[director, in French]
Welcome to our international tournament.

19:39.583 --> 19:40.750
This is a single round-robin event.

19:40.833 --> 19:43.250
Everyone plays everyone.

19:43.333 --> 19:45.791
There are six players and five rounds.

19:45.875 --> 19:48.416
One round a day for five days

19:49.000 --> 19:51.500
with one day off for adjournments.

19:53.166 --> 19:55.833
Places in our cross table
have been chosen by lot.

19:55.916 --> 19:58.625
Colors have been chosen accordingly.

19:59.208 --> 20:02.583
[reporter, in English] Mr. Borgov, what's
it like to compete with younger players,

20:02.666 --> 20:04.875
and how much longer
do you think you'll play?

20:05.916 --> 20:08.083
[Borgov speaking Russian]

20:23.958 --> 20:27.250
[in English] "I feel good,
as good as I felt when I was 4 years old,

20:27.333 --> 20:28.791
and played my first game."

20:29.791 --> 20:30.791
"Chess still…

20:31.541 --> 20:33.208
excites me in the same way."

20:33.291 --> 20:35.000
"I have no plans to stop playing,

20:35.083 --> 20:36.791
and I'll…

20:37.541 --> 20:40.125
likely die with my head on a chessboard."

20:40.208 --> 20:41.208
[all laugh]

20:41.291 --> 20:45.083
Miss Harmon, what do you say
to those in the Chess Federation

20:45.166 --> 20:47.500
who accuse you of being too glamorous

20:47.583 --> 20:49.166
to be a serious chess player?

20:52.375 --> 20:54.708
I would say
that it's much easier to play chess

20:54.791 --> 20:56.708
without the burden of an Adam's apple.

20:56.791 --> 20:58.000
[all chuckle]

20:58.083 --> 21:00.875
So, how are you feeling
about your match with Alec Bergland?

21:01.791 --> 21:03.333
[Beth] I'm looking forward to it.

21:03.416 --> 21:05.583
[reporter 2]
Does that mean you think you can beat him?

21:05.666 --> 21:07.416
It means that I have to beat him.

21:08.416 --> 21:13.166
Miss Harmon, do you feel good
about rematch with Grandmaster Borgov?

21:13.250 --> 21:14.666
[Beth] Very good.

21:14.750 --> 21:17.500
I slept on the plane,
so I arrived in Paris with no jet lag.

21:17.583 --> 21:19.250
I'm very well rested.

21:19.333 --> 21:23.541
At night, I stay in my room,
and study Mr. Borgov's old games.

21:23.625 --> 21:25.916
Including the one against you
in Mexico City?

21:28.541 --> 21:30.208
[in Russian] Especially that one.

21:32.666 --> 21:36.000
[director, in French] The time control
is 40 moves in two and half hours.

21:36.541 --> 21:37.416
Any questions?

21:38.166 --> 21:39.000
Very well.

21:39.083 --> 21:40.416
Good luck to each of you.

21:40.500 --> 21:41.333
May the best man,

21:41.416 --> 21:42.333
or woman,

21:42.416 --> 21:43.583
win.

21:43.666 --> 21:45.583
-[button clicks]
-[exciting music playing]

22:42.958 --> 22:44.166
I'm sorry, Mademoiselle?

22:44.250 --> 22:46.958
Excuse me. Would it be possible
to have an autograph?

22:55.000 --> 22:55.833
[button clicks]

23:01.208 --> 23:02.041
[button clicks]

23:44.833 --> 23:45.875
[applauding]

23:52.916 --> 23:54.375
Mademoiselle. [clears throat]

23:55.250 --> 23:56.875
[in French] Tomorrow, it's you…

23:57.875 --> 23:59.375
…against Grandmaster Borgov.

24:02.625 --> 24:04.500
[pensive music playing]

24:39.291 --> 24:41.000
[phone ringing]

24:44.416 --> 24:45.458
[phone ringing]

24:46.875 --> 24:47.708
Hello?

24:48.083 --> 24:51.208
[woman] What, you thought you could sneak
into town without me knowing?

24:51.875 --> 24:53.000
Who is this?

24:53.083 --> 24:54.583
And now you insult me.

24:57.291 --> 24:59.291
-Cleo?
-A very sad Cleo.

24:59.375 --> 25:02.666
[laughs] I'm sorry. I was just…

25:03.875 --> 25:05.916
-Where are you?
-Downstairs.

25:07.250 --> 25:08.791
-Here?
-I thought you might come down

25:08.875 --> 25:10.000
and join me for a drink.

25:12.708 --> 25:14.125
I have a match tomorrow.

25:14.208 --> 25:17.000
One drink, and then you go back up
and resume your rigors.

25:18.875 --> 25:19.875
It's the final.

25:20.375 --> 25:22.041
I should probably sleep.

25:22.125 --> 25:23.250
Of course you should.

25:23.791 --> 25:24.708
I understand.

25:25.375 --> 25:27.750
But maybe tomorrow night?

25:27.833 --> 25:30.083
Well, who knows
where I'll be so far in the future?

25:30.166 --> 25:32.833
But, um, I wish you luck in your match.

25:34.291 --> 25:35.125
Thank you.

25:36.083 --> 25:37.500
You know, it's a lovely bar.

25:38.375 --> 25:41.000
I think I'll go toast
your success on my own.

25:42.750 --> 25:43.833
Sweet dreams.

25:47.083 --> 25:48.041
[receiver clatters]

25:58.791 --> 26:01.541
-[indistinct conversations]
-[man singing in French]

26:07.583 --> 26:08.416
Hi.

26:09.750 --> 26:13.000
So, the pretty girl has taste
to go with her other gifts, huh?

26:14.625 --> 26:16.000
You make me sick, you know.

26:16.875 --> 26:18.875
Thank you, so do you.

26:20.500 --> 26:22.333
Now, just one drink.

26:23.166 --> 26:24.416
I wanna get to bed early.

26:25.208 --> 26:26.041
Okay.

26:26.833 --> 26:29.208
So, what will you have then,
for your one drink?

26:29.791 --> 26:31.750
Must be special if it is your only one.

26:33.291 --> 26:34.291
What are you having?

26:35.250 --> 26:36.833
It's called pastis.

26:37.958 --> 26:39.916
Very Parisian, very ordinary.

26:41.208 --> 26:42.041
Here, try it.

26:50.375 --> 26:51.583
Tastes like licorice.

26:51.666 --> 26:52.500
Mmm.

26:53.000 --> 26:53.833
The anise.

26:55.000 --> 26:55.833
I like it.

26:56.958 --> 27:00.208
-[Beth] I could see myself living here.
-[Cleo] I could see it, too.

27:00.708 --> 27:03.041
A little pied-à-terre
on the Rue des Capucines,

27:03.125 --> 27:04.583
or the Boulevard Raspail.

27:05.666 --> 27:07.625
In a few years, I'll be world champion.

27:08.166 --> 27:09.541
I can live wherever I want.

27:10.208 --> 27:12.000
It will be much sooner than that.

27:12.541 --> 27:14.125
If I lived here…

27:16.041 --> 27:19.666
I would go to plays, and concerts, and…

27:20.250 --> 27:23.250
I would eat lunch
in a different cafe every day. [laughs]

27:23.333 --> 27:25.666
And I would dress the way
that women do here, you know?

27:25.750 --> 27:29.291
So smart with their nice dresses,
and their perfect haircuts.

27:29.375 --> 27:31.666
You already have
so much more than they do.

27:32.708 --> 27:35.000
And something that none of them have.

27:36.041 --> 27:36.958
Talent.

27:38.000 --> 27:40.666
And that can give you a life
that anyone would envy.

27:43.041 --> 27:45.000
There's nothing keeping me in Kentucky.

27:46.375 --> 27:47.875
The possibilities are endless.

27:48.708 --> 27:51.291
And one of those possibilities
is staring at you.

27:57.750 --> 28:00.000
No, they're looking at you.

28:00.750 --> 28:01.750
I think not.

28:02.750 --> 28:04.000
You are very beautiful.

28:05.708 --> 28:08.250
-I don't see myself that way.
-Then you are blind.

28:08.333 --> 28:09.291
Do you like to fuck?

28:10.208 --> 28:11.833
-Cleo!
-What?

28:11.916 --> 28:14.291
I make it easier for you.
Did you like to fuck Benny?

28:15.833 --> 28:16.666
Sometimes.

28:16.750 --> 28:18.208
How romantic. [scoffs]

28:19.291 --> 28:20.875
And have you ever been in love?

28:22.791 --> 28:23.791
Not with Benny.

28:23.875 --> 28:24.708
Of course not.

28:24.791 --> 28:27.875
No woman can compete
with Benny's love for himself.

28:31.166 --> 28:32.791
So, we are still in love?

28:35.291 --> 28:36.250
What's his name?

28:38.416 --> 28:39.333
Townes.

28:42.208 --> 28:43.833
To unrequited love.

28:44.958 --> 28:46.791
And to stupid men.

28:47.583 --> 28:48.416
Exactly.

28:54.208 --> 28:55.916
Let's see how many lies they tell.

28:56.625 --> 28:57.458
Excuse me?

29:09.833 --> 29:10.666
[knocking]

29:10.750 --> 29:13.208
Mademoiselle?
Mademoiselle Harmon, vous êtes là?

29:13.833 --> 29:15.291
[water splashing]

29:15.375 --> 29:16.208
[panting]

29:16.291 --> 29:18.500
-[knocking on door]
-Mademoiselle, on vous attend.

29:21.333 --> 29:23.000
Je descends tout de suite.

29:23.083 --> 29:23.916
Okay?

29:26.541 --> 29:28.541
[bell tolling in distance]

29:37.833 --> 29:38.750
[door closes]

29:45.500 --> 29:46.333
[panting]

29:48.000 --> 29:49.125
Thank you.

29:53.541 --> 29:55.250
[reporters clamoring in French]

30:11.375 --> 30:12.458
I'm sorry.

30:20.291 --> 30:21.125
[clears throat]

30:23.333 --> 30:24.416
[chess clock ticking]

30:36.750 --> 30:37.583
[slurps]

30:40.083 --> 30:41.541
[dramatic violin note]

30:43.458 --> 30:45.041
[chess clock continues ticking]

30:46.208 --> 30:47.375
[dramatic violin note]

30:52.208 --> 30:53.375
[dramatic violin note]

30:53.458 --> 30:55.583
[slurps, gulps]

30:57.791 --> 30:59.416
[dramatic violin continues]

31:15.041 --> 31:16.000
[sniffles]

32:04.708 --> 32:06.083
[speaking inaudibly]

32:08.208 --> 32:09.041
[sniffles]

33:19.166 --> 33:20.791
[music fading]

33:20.875 --> 33:21.708
I resign.

33:28.083 --> 33:30.083
[crowd applauding]

33:31.583 --> 33:33.291
[Benny] There's a rumor you were drunk.

33:33.375 --> 33:34.666
[Beth] I wasn't drunk.

33:35.250 --> 33:36.583
[Benny] Or hungover, then.

33:37.250 --> 33:39.375
[Beth] I could have been stone-cold sober.

33:40.416 --> 33:42.291
It wouldn't have made
the slightest difference.

33:42.375 --> 33:43.708
[Benny] I don't believe that.

33:44.208 --> 33:46.583
What time do you get in?
I can come pick you up.

33:47.083 --> 33:48.833
[Beth] I'm going back to Lexington.

33:49.583 --> 33:50.583
I need to be alone.

33:50.666 --> 33:53.291
[Benny]
That is the opposite of what you need.

33:53.375 --> 33:56.583
Beth, please just come to New York.
We can talk it out.

33:59.541 --> 34:02.000
-Beth?
-[Beth] Thank you, Benny.

34:02.750 --> 34:03.583
For everything.

34:04.208 --> 34:07.500
[Benny] You shouldn't be by yourself.
You know what happens.

34:07.583 --> 34:09.125
[Beth] Maybe that's what I want.

34:09.208 --> 34:13.125
-[Benny] What, to get drunk?
-[Beth] Yeah, good and drunk.

34:13.958 --> 34:14.958
Fucking bombed.

34:15.708 --> 34:17.541
And maybe high, too. Why not?

34:18.166 --> 34:20.875
-[Benny] You wouldn't if you were with me.
-[Beth] I know.

34:21.833 --> 34:24.083
[Benny] What if I said,
"Go ahead, get drunk"?

34:24.583 --> 34:25.583
Would you come then?

34:26.166 --> 34:28.750
[Beth] Benny, I don't know what I'm doing.

34:31.875 --> 34:32.708
Or going to do.

34:40.291 --> 34:42.291
[melancholy music playing]

34:48.291 --> 34:50.458
[phone rings]

34:51.416 --> 34:52.250
[door closes]

34:54.250 --> 34:56.458
[phone rings]

35:00.000 --> 35:01.583
-Hello.
-This is Dick Chennault.

35:05.250 --> 35:07.208
-Um…
-Your lawyer.

35:08.625 --> 35:09.458
Oh.

35:10.458 --> 35:13.875
I tried to get you three times yesterday,
and the day before. Where you been?

35:16.000 --> 35:16.875
In Paris.

35:17.583 --> 35:18.416
Playing chess.

35:18.958 --> 35:20.166
How sweet it must be.

35:22.041 --> 35:23.958
What is it I can do for you,
Mr. Chennault?

35:24.041 --> 35:26.791
Uh, it's, uh, it's Wheatley.
He doesn't wanna sign.

35:28.166 --> 35:29.333
Sign what?

35:29.416 --> 35:31.000
Title for the house.

35:32.291 --> 35:34.333
Can you get over here
so we can work it out?

35:35.333 --> 35:37.958
I don't see why you would need me.
You're the lawyer.

35:39.458 --> 35:41.958
And he said he would sign
whatever was necessary, so…

35:42.041 --> 35:44.791
Oh, well, apparently,
he's changed his mind.

35:48.625 --> 35:49.916
[knocking on door]

36:00.250 --> 36:01.083
Come in.

36:05.333 --> 36:06.166
[Dick] Beth.

36:07.916 --> 36:09.458
Mr. Wheatley has a proposal.

36:10.083 --> 36:13.041
You can live here while you're looking
for something permanent.

36:13.958 --> 36:16.458
I thought I could keep the house
if I made the payments.

36:16.541 --> 36:17.583
Uh, Mr. Wheatley…

36:18.416 --> 36:20.208
says you misconstrued him.

36:21.041 --> 36:24.541
He, uh, claims he was just permitting you
to stay in the house, uh…

36:25.125 --> 36:26.250
until you got settled.

36:27.000 --> 36:27.916
That's not true.

36:29.541 --> 36:30.666
He said I could have it.

36:32.416 --> 36:33.250
Remember?

36:37.416 --> 36:38.875
Can't you even look at me?

36:41.125 --> 36:43.500
-You adopted me. Can't you talk to me?
-Alma.

36:44.666 --> 36:46.666
-Alma wanted a child.
-[Beth] You signed the papers.

36:46.750 --> 36:50.250
-You took on a responsibility.
-Alma wanted to adopt you, not me.

36:50.333 --> 36:51.875
You're not entitled to everything I own,

36:51.958 --> 36:54.041
just 'cause I signed
some papers to shut her up.

36:55.333 --> 36:56.291
Not that it worked.

36:57.666 --> 36:59.458
You adopted me.

37:01.083 --> 37:02.083
I didn't ask you to.

37:03.416 --> 37:06.166
-You're my legal father.
-The money in this house is mine!

37:06.708 --> 37:08.875
No smart-assed orphan
is gonna take it away from me.

37:08.958 --> 37:11.708
Oh, I'm not an orphan.
I'm your daughter.

37:11.791 --> 37:13.166
Not in my book, you aren't.

37:14.166 --> 37:16.500
I don't give a shit
what your goddamn lawyer says.

37:16.583 --> 37:20.000
Or what Alma said, either.
That woman could not keep her mouth shut.

37:20.083 --> 37:22.375
I thought the piano would help, it didn't.

37:22.458 --> 37:23.875
So, here you are.

37:23.958 --> 37:26.000
It's all so pathetic.

37:29.458 --> 37:30.916
Did you ever hear her play?

37:32.333 --> 37:33.333
Of course.

37:33.416 --> 37:35.250
Yes, but did you ever really listen?

37:36.666 --> 37:39.125
Alma was not pathetic,
she was stuck. There's a difference.

37:39.250 --> 37:41.125
She didn't know how to get out of it.

37:41.666 --> 37:42.750
Pathetic, well…

37:45.000 --> 37:46.208
I'm looking at pathetic.

37:49.750 --> 37:51.833
What do you want from Beth, Mr. Wheatley?

37:51.916 --> 37:55.000
-I want her out. I'm selling the house.
-Sell it to me.

37:55.916 --> 37:56.958
What are you talking about?

37:57.958 --> 37:58.791
I'll buy it.

37:59.833 --> 38:01.166
I'll pay whatever your equity is.

38:01.250 --> 38:03.583
-No, it's worth more than that now.
-How much more?

38:05.583 --> 38:06.791
I'd need 7,000.

38:06.875 --> 38:08.416
Your equity is less than five.

38:08.500 --> 38:10.750
It's seven. I'll show you the receipts.

38:14.166 --> 38:15.000
Fine.

38:16.458 --> 38:17.291
Seven thousand.

38:20.125 --> 38:21.750
-You have that much?
-[Beth] Yes.

38:22.416 --> 38:25.500
But I will be subtracting
what I paid to bury Mother.

38:28.416 --> 38:29.791
I'll show you the receipts.

38:31.666 --> 38:33.458
[sighs] It's too hot in here.

38:39.375 --> 38:40.208
Well…

38:41.291 --> 38:42.125
good luck.

38:47.083 --> 38:47.916
[door closes]

38:48.000 --> 38:52.375
I'll, uh… [clears throat]
…send over the paperwork in a day or so.

38:53.500 --> 38:54.750
Um… [clears throat]

39:02.750 --> 39:05.375
-[door opens and closes]
-[sighs]

39:06.625 --> 39:08.791
["Tut Tut Tut Tut"
by Gillian Hill playing]

39:08.875 --> 39:12.166
♪ Tut, tut, tut, tut, tut, tut, tut ♪

39:12.708 --> 39:16.625
♪ Voilà, c'est comme ça
Depuis dix heures ce matin ♪

39:17.083 --> 39:20.708
♪ Ce n'est pas libre
Ce n'est pas libre ♪

39:20.791 --> 39:24.083
♪ Je sens la colère
Qui me fait trembler les mains ♪

39:24.833 --> 39:28.250
♪ Ce n'est pas libre
Ce n'est pas libre ♪

39:28.333 --> 39:32.125
♪ Je perds mon sang-froid
En écoutant cet air-là ♪

39:32.208 --> 39:35.625
♪ Tut, tut, tut, tut, tut, tut, tut ♪

39:39.750 --> 39:42.875
♪ J'ai tout essayé
Mais c'est pareil chaque fois ♪

39:44.208 --> 39:47.458
♪ Ce n'est pas libre
Ce n'est pas libre ♪

39:47.541 --> 39:51.000
♪ J'ai téléphoné du petit café en bas ♪

39:51.916 --> 39:55.416
♪ Ce n'est pas libre
Ce n'est pas libre ♪

39:55.500 --> 39:59.125
♪ Se moquant de moi
Chaque fois, j'entends cet air-là ♪

39:59.208 --> 40:02.708
♪ Tut, tut, tut, tut, tut, tut, tut ♪

40:03.791 --> 40:06.833
♪ Pourtant j'aurais juré ♪

40:06.916 --> 40:10.125
♪ Que ce garçon m'aimait ♪

40:11.041 --> 40:14.041
♪ Après m'avoir embrassée ♪

40:14.125 --> 40:18.000
♪ Il me disait
Jamais je ne t'oublierai ♪

40:18.083 --> 40:21.916
♪ Mais le téléphone
Semble me dire à l'oreille ♪

40:22.583 --> 40:25.958
♪ Il n'est pas libre
Il n'est pas libre… ♪

40:26.041 --> 40:26.875
Hi.

40:27.833 --> 40:28.916
You want another job?

40:30.250 --> 40:33.500
♪ Il n'est plus libre
Il n'est plus libre ♪

40:33.583 --> 40:37.458
♪ Et tu y penseras
Chaque fois que tu entendras ♪

40:37.541 --> 40:40.708
♪ Tut, tut, tut, tut, tut, tut, tut ♪

40:49.666 --> 40:51.083
♪ Ce n'est pas libre ♪

40:51.166 --> 40:54.958
-♪ Tut tut tut tut tut tut tut tut ♪
-♪ Ce n'est pas libre ♪

40:55.041 --> 40:56.833
-♪ Tut tut tut tut ♪
-♪ Ce n'est pas libre ♪

41:05.000 --> 41:06.500
♪ Ce n'est pas libre ♪

41:06.583 --> 41:09.875
-♪ Tut tut tut tut tut tut tut tut ♪
-♪ Ce n'est pas libre… ♪

41:09.958 --> 41:10.791
[door closes]

41:11.791 --> 41:12.625
[keys clatter]

41:30.958 --> 41:32.958
[pensive music playing]

41:36.666 --> 41:37.833
[man] Dear Miss Harmon,

41:38.416 --> 41:41.416
as we have been unable
to reach you by telephone,

41:41.500 --> 41:45.541
we are writing to determine your interest
in the support of Christian Crusade

41:45.625 --> 41:48.666
in your forthcoming competition
in the USSR.

41:50.458 --> 41:53.500
Christian Crusade
is a nonprofit organization

41:53.583 --> 41:57.333
dedicated to the opening
of closed doors to the message of Christ.

41:59.541 --> 42:03.041
We have found your career
as a trainee of a Christian institution,

42:03.125 --> 42:05.333
the Methuen Home, noteworthy.

42:06.208 --> 42:08.916
We would like to help you
in your forthcoming struggle,

42:09.000 --> 42:12.041
since we share your Christian ideals
and aspirations.

42:14.291 --> 42:16.458
If you are interested in our support,

42:16.541 --> 42:18.875
please contact our offices in Houston.

42:20.875 --> 42:23.458
Yours in Christ, Crawford Walker.

42:24.458 --> 42:26.416
[Benny] Take the money. They're loaded.

42:26.500 --> 42:28.666
[Beth] They'd pay for my ticket to Russia?

42:28.750 --> 42:29.708
More than that.

42:30.375 --> 42:34.000
If you need to play another match before,
they'll back you,

42:34.083 --> 42:36.625
and if you ask them,
they'll fly me out there with you.

42:37.458 --> 42:40.625
Separate rooms, of course,
considering their views.

42:40.708 --> 42:42.000
Why would they pay so much?

42:42.083 --> 42:45.541
They want us to beat Communists for Jesus.

42:46.458 --> 42:49.875
These are the same people that paid
for part of my way two years ago.

42:52.916 --> 42:54.041
Are you, uh…

42:55.041 --> 42:56.166
coming to New York?

42:58.458 --> 43:00.166
I have to stay in Kentucky a bit longer.

43:00.791 --> 43:04.750
I have a tournament in San Francisco,
and I need to take care of this place now.

43:07.000 --> 43:09.708
I'm fine, Benny, really.

43:10.458 --> 43:11.291
How are you?

43:11.916 --> 43:12.750
I'm managing.

43:13.416 --> 43:14.666
[distant traffic sounds]

43:15.583 --> 43:16.416
I miss you.

43:23.041 --> 43:26.208
Study the game pamphlets
from the last Moscow Invitational.

43:27.083 --> 43:29.708
-I'm not even sure I'm gonna go.
-Just do it, Beth.

43:30.333 --> 43:31.666
Write the Jesus people back.

43:31.750 --> 43:34.500
Tell them you will take all the help
that they can give you.

44:13.791 --> 44:15.000
[pieces clatter softly]

44:24.000 --> 44:24.833
[sniffs]

44:46.416 --> 44:48.416
[gentle piano music playing]

44:56.708 --> 45:00.083
I will have the asparagus vinaigrette
as an appetizer

45:00.166 --> 45:01.958
while I think about my main course.

45:02.041 --> 45:03.333
[waiter] Very well, Miss Harmon.

45:03.416 --> 45:05.125
And would you care for a cocktail?

45:06.666 --> 45:08.375
No, uh, Coke is fine.

45:10.875 --> 45:11.708
Actually…

45:13.333 --> 45:14.333
I'll have a Gibson.

45:15.375 --> 45:16.208
On the rocks.

45:17.458 --> 45:18.416
[waiter] Of course.

